        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894A.00/5–1949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Taipei</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-19">May 19,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received May 19—10:29 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>176. Provincial government and Taiwan garrison today jointly proclaimed martial
                    law here effective May 20. All ports closed except Keelung, Kaohsiung and
                    Makung. Execution for usual offenses.</p>
                <p>Repeated EmbOff Canton 39, Shanghai 141, Nanking 140.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
